# ========================================
# Security Notes
# ========================================
#
# Frontend-Exposed Variables (NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix):
# - Safe to expose in browser context
# - Used for client-side LIFF and Supabase operations
#
# Secret Variables (server-side only):
# - LINE_CHANNEL_ACCESS_TOKEN: Can send LINE messages
# - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY: Full database access
# - Never expose these in frontend code
#
# Authentication & Access Control:
# - LINE LIFF provides authentication for members-only access
# - Supabase RLS policies enforce data access rules
# - Service role key bypasses RLS - use with caution
#
# Deployment Security:
# - Use different values for development/production
# - Regular rotation of secret keys recommended
# - Monitor access logs for suspicious activity
